<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Hardened-runtime entitlements for the notarized macOS build.

  Why each entitlement exists:

  • com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit
  • com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory
      WKWebView's JavaScriptCore needs to allocate executable pages at
      runtime to JIT-compile JS. Without these two, the app boots to a
      blank window and crashes the WebContent process as soon as any
      non-trivial script runs. This is the single most common cause of
      a "worked unsigned, crashes after notarization" failure.

  • com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
      Tauri's bundle ships its own dynamic libraries (tao, wry, webkit
      shims) that aren't signed by Apple's Team ID — they're signed by
      us at bundle time. Hardened runtime's library validation will
      refuse to load them unless this is disabled. Non-App-Store apps
      routinely set this.

  • com.apple.security.network.client
      The Marketplace tab fetches the server catalog over HTTPS from
      GitHub. Without this, the request silently fails with NSURLError
      on a hardened-runtime build.

  What we deliberately do NOT grant:

  • com.apple.security.app-sandbox — we are direct-distributed, not
    App Store, and the whole point of the app is reading/writing the
    user's Claude config files scattered across ~/Library, ~/.claude,
    and %APPDATA%. Sandboxing would break every core feature.
  • Network server, camera, microphone, contacts, location, etc. — we
    don't need any of them and granting them unnecessarily weakens the
    app's trust posture.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
